---
const faqItems = [
  {
    id: "1",
    question: "What Is an Xbox Gamertag?",
    answer: `An Xbox gamertag is your public name on Xbox. It is the name other players see on your profile, in multiplayer lobbies, on leaderboards, and across Xbox services.

Your gamertag is a big part of your gaming identity. A clean and memorable name can make a stronger first impression, while a messy or hard-to-read tag is easier to forget.

That is why choosing the right Xbox name matters. A good gamertag should be easy to read, easy to remember, and a good fit for your style.`
  },
  {
    id: "2",
    question: "How Does the Xbox Gamertag Generator Work?",
    answer: `This Xbox Gamertag Generator helps you create name ideas based on the options you choose.

You can pick a gender style, theme, language, and character limit, then generate a list of Xbox-ready name ideas in seconds. The goal is to give you names that are cleaner, more creative, and easier to use than random usernames.

It is a fast way to get ideas when you are stuck, rebranding, or trying to find a better Xbox identity.`
  },
  {
    id: "3",
    question: "What Makes a Good Xbox Gamertag?",
    answer: `A good Xbox gamertag is usually simple, clear, and memorable.

The best names are:
• Easy to read
• Easy to say out loud
• Short enough to fit well on profiles and scoreboards
• Unique without looking messy
• A good match for your personality or gaming style

If a name looks clean, feels natural, and is still easy to remember after a few minutes, it is usually a strong option.`
  },
  {
    id: "4",
    question: "What Are the Current Xbox Gamertag Rules?",
    answer: `Modern Xbox gamertags use a base-name system. The base gamertag can be up to 12 characters long, and spaces count toward that limit.

If another player already uses the same base name, Xbox may add a numeric suffix to help keep the full gamertag unique. That means some duplicate names can still be used in the modern system.

It is also smart to avoid offensive terms, impersonation, and overly messy formatting when choosing a name.`
  },
  {
    id: "5",
    question: "Can I Create a Funny or Unique Xbox Gamertag?",
    answer: `Yes. A funny or unique gamertag can work very well if it is still clean and readable.

Many players like tags that are:
• Funny
• Clever
• Dark or competitive
• Minimal and clean
• Based on a theme or favorite style

The best funny names are usually short and easy to understand. The best unique names stand out without relying too much on random numbers or cluttered symbols.`
  },
  {
    id: "6",
    question: "How Do I Claim a New Xbox Gamertag?",
    answer: `Once you find a name you like, you can change your Xbox gamertag through your Xbox console, the Xbox app, or your Microsoft/Xbox account settings on the web.

Your first gamertag change is free. After that, additional changes may require a fee, and the cost can vary by region and currency.

Before you claim a new name, it is a good idea to double-check that it still looks clean, readable, and worth keeping long term.`
  }
];

const faqSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": faqItems.map((item) => ({
    "@type": "Question",
    "name": item.question,
    "acceptedAnswer": {
      "@type": "Answer",
      "text": item.answer
    }
  }))
};

---
<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(faqSchema)} />
<!-- Full-width light grey FAQ section -->
<section
  class="py-10 md:py-20"
  style="background-color: hsl(220 14% 96%); width: 100vw; position: relative; left: 50%; right: 50%; margin-left: -50vw; margin-right: -50vw;"
>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">

    <!-- Header -->
    <div class="text-center mb-10 sm:mb-12">
      <div
        class="inline-flex items-center mb-4"
        style="background: hsl(107 76% 26% / 0.08); border: 1px solid hsl(107 76% 26% / 0.25); border-radius: 3px; padding: 3px 12px;"
      >
        <span
          style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif; font-size:10px; font-weight:700; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color: hsl(107 76% 26%);"
        >
          FAQ
        </span>
      </div>

      <h2
        class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-3"
        style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif; color: hsl(218 30% 9%); letter-spacing: -0.02em;"
      >
        Xbox Gamertag FAQ
      </h2>

      <p
        class="text-sm max-w-2xl mx-auto"
        style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif; color: hsl(215 16% 47%); line-height: 1.6;"
      >
        Answers to common questions about Xbox gamertags, naming rules, and how to choose a better Xbox name.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Accordion list -->
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-3" id="faq-list">
      {faqItems.map((item) => (
        <div
          class="faq-item w-full overflow-hidden rounded-lg"
          data-faq-id={item.id}
          style="background: #ffffff; border: 1px solid hsl(220 13% 91%); box-shadow: 0 2px 8px hsl(218 30% 9% / 0.06); transition: border-color 0.2s ease, box-shadow 0.2s ease;"
        >
          <button
            class="faq-toggle w-full flex items-center justify-between gap-4 text-left px-5 py-4 sm:px-6 sm:py-5"
            type="button"
            aria-expanded="false"
            data-id={item.id}
            style="background: transparent; border: none; cursor: pointer; outline: none; touch-action: manipulation;"
          >
            <span
              class="faq-question text-sm sm:text-base font-semibold flex-1"
              style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif; color: hsl(218 20% 16%); line-height: 1.4; transition: color 0.2s ease;"
            >
              {item.question}
            </span>

            <svg
              class="faq-chevron flex-shrink-0"
              width="18"
              height="18"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              fill="none"
              stroke="currentColor"
              stroke-width="2.5"
              stroke-linecap="round"
              stroke-linejoin="round"
              aria-hidden="true"
              style="color: hsl(107 76% 26%); transition: transform 0.25s cubic-bezier(0.4,0,0.2,1); flex-shrink: 0;"
            >
              <polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9" />
            </svg>
          </button>

          <div
            class="faq-content"
            aria-hidden="true"
            style="max-height: 0; overflow: hidden; transition: max-height 0.35s cubic-bezier(0.4,0,0.2,1);"
          >
            <div class="mx-5 sm:mx-6" style="height:1px; background: hsl(220 13% 91%);"></div>

            <div class="px-5 sm:px-6 py-4 sm:py-5 flex flex-col gap-4">
              {item.answer
                .split("\n\n")
                .filter(Boolean)
                .map((part) => (
                  <p
                    class="text-sm leading-relaxed whitespace-pre-line"
                    style="font-family:'Inter',sans-serif; color: hsl(215 16% 47%); line-height: 1.75;"
                  >
                    {part.trim()}
                  </p>
                ))}
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
<style>
  .faq-item:hover {
    background: #ffffff !important;
    border-color: hsl(107 76% 26% / 0.3) !important;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 16px hsl(218 30% 9% / 0.1) !important;
  }

  .faq-item.is-open {
    background: #ffffff !important;
    border-color: hsl(107 76% 26% / 0.4) !important;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 20px hsl(218 30% 9% / 0.1) !important;
  }

  .faq-item.is-open .faq-question {
    color: hsl(107 76% 26%) !important;
  }

  .faq-item.is-open .faq-chevron {
    transform: rotate(180deg) !important;
  }

  .faq-toggle:hover {
    background-color: hsl(220 13% 97%) !important;
  }

  .faq-content p {
    color: hsl(215 16% 47%) !important;
  }

  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    .faq-content {
      transition: none !important;
    }

    .faq-chevron {
      transition: none !important;
    }
  }
</style>

<script is:inline>
  function initFaq() {
    document.querySelectorAll('.faq-toggle').forEach(function (btn) {
      if (btn.dataset.bound === 'true') return;
      btn.dataset.bound = 'true';

      btn.addEventListener('click', function () {
        var item = btn.closest('.faq-item');
        var content = item ? item.querySelector('.faq-content') : null;
        if (!item || !content) return;

        var isOpen = item.classList.contains('is-open');

        document.querySelectorAll('.faq-item').forEach(function (el) {
          el.classList.remove('is-open');

          var c = el.querySelector('.faq-content');
          if (c) c.style.maxHeight = '0';

          var t = el.querySelector('.faq-toggle');
          if (t) t.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'false');
        });

        if (!isOpen) {
          item.classList.add('is-open');
          content.style.maxHeight = content.scrollHeight + 'px';
          btn.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'true');
        }
      });
    });
  }

  if (document.readyState === 'loading') {
    document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', initFaq, { once: true });
  } else {
    initFaq();
  }

  document.addEventListener('astro:page-load', initFaq);
</script>